verbose_text: In multivariate analysis Independent risk factors for survival were serum AFP level> 400 ng/ml (HR = 2.07, CI = 2.03-3.36, P = 0.039), TTV> 65.5 cm 3 (HR = 2.16, CI = 2.08-3.12, P = 0.05), microvascular invasion (HR = 1.02, CI = 1.14-1.83, P = 0.012), postoperative decompensation (HR = 1.68, CI = 1.56-2.93, P = 0.041) (XREF_TABLE).
